The paper specifically focuses on population-based algorithms, which are a type of optimisation algorithm that maintain a population of candidate solutions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which is specifically concerned with optimisation algorithms. 

The paper also discusses the importance of sampling strategies and efficiency, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper also uses theoretical and empirical analyses, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). 

Finally, the paper discusses the implications of structural bias on the performance of population-based algorithms, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
